field.Element:Text: (DEBUG) Flag raised, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Welcome, Master! This is your home, the “Mog House,” kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I'm a moogle! We moogles like taking care of houses and items! Nice to meet you, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I'll tell you all about your Mog House, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
First, the basics, kupo!
Open your main menu, Master. The button at the very bottom changes to “Mog House” when you're in your Mog House, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Press it and the “Mog House” menu will appear! Everything you can do in your Mog House is there, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There are lots of things you can do in your Mog House, kupo! It can be too much for some masters, kupo...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: So I'll teach you about each one of them! Ask me what you want to know about, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Choose the Mog House command you want to know about, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What do you want to know about?
≺Selection Dialog≻The Mog Safe.
Storage.
The Delivery Box.
Changing jobs.
Gardening.
Changing the layout.
Mog House invitations.
I got it, thanks, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The Mog Safe is where I keep items that you can't carry! It's an especially secure and solid safe, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can only put so many items in it, kupo... But I'll guard them even if it means my life, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The Delivery Box is where you can send letters to friends and receive items from various places, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You should take the items from your Delivery Box and put them in your inventory when they arrive, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If your Delivery Box is full, no more deliveries can be made, and you can't send any mail either, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can send items and gil to your friends with the “Send” command, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: (Sometimes, if a special force takes hold, you can even deliver items with the "Exclusive" attribute, kupo...!)≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Changing people's jobs is a secret ability only we moogles can use, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I take off all your equipment and take you to a mysterious place, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And...the rest is a secret, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: All moogles like taking care of plants, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As long as you have a flowerpot and seeds, I'll make it my personal responsibility to look after the plants you raise, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: This Mog House is your very own room, kupo! But it's still a little bare, kupo...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It needs some furniture and maybe some paintings to make it more cozy, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you find any during your travels, I'll help you lay them out, kupo! I can't wait, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Storage space becomes available when you place furniture in your Mog House using the “Layout” command, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
It's almost exactly the same as using your Mog Safe, kupo!
Leave your items here for me to look after, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can invite party and alliance members into your Mog House, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can show off your expensive furniture, have tea parties, plan your next great adventure--the possibilities are endless, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Are you sure, kupo? You know everything about your Mog House, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Are you sure?
≺Selection Dialog≻I'm sure!
Maybe I'm not so sure...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And finally, a little bit of advice!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you ever run into any problems, just ask your fellow adventurers for help!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you type “/ae Hello!”, then your message will be heard by many people.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you type “/ae” followed by your issue or question, other adventurers will help you!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Remember that you can only do this while in town, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Okay, kupo!
Good luck on your adventuring, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Do you want me to teach you about your Mog House again, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Ask about your Mog House again?
≺Selection Dialog≻Don't ask.
Ask.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
Over the mountains and the rolling hills,
I'll go wherever my master wills.♪≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
Master!
I traveled all the way here at your bidding, kupo! Even a Rent-a-Room needs a moogle, kupo!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: But there are a few things you can't do in a Rent-a-Room, kupo. Select “Mog House” from the main menu and check, kupo!≺Prompt≻

At once so glorious and so ghastly, and just for you!

We must make repairs before we have water up to my little wings!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I figure all I'll need is a good ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻#≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻, ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻ ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻$ａ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻, and ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻ ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻$ｂ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ to have this fixed up good as new, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Could I trouble you to track them down?
While you're out, I'll patch up the other problem spots.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
And do hurry, Master!
Lest you return to find your poor moogle friend lying prostrate in a pernicious puddle of rainwater, kupo...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Thank you, Master, but our leak is in another Mog House!
Bring this to me when we're back home in ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[San d'Oria/Bastok/Windurst], won't you, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You've found them, kupo! I knew I could count on you.
That's what I tell all my moogle buddies. “Why, my master is the boldest, brightest, bestest master of them all!”
Now we just take these, and...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Kupoooooo～there you have it! Better than new!
Why, a bevy of wild buffalo could barge in here this second and it wouldn't budge an ilm, I say!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Which reminds me, I went ahead and relayed the requisite reports to my manager at the MHMU.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
But wouldn't you know it, kupo?
It seems there's been a trifling bit of trouble at one of our Rent-a-Rooms in Jeuno as well!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You know the one, right across from Durable Shields.
Whatever could have gone wrong, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Well, there's nothing to be learned lollygagging around here.
Come, Master, we're off to Jeuno!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Little did anyone suspect that this
     would prove to be only the beginning
     of a harrowing nightmare unheard of
     in the annals of mooglekind...≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Hang on! I have an amazing announcement!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The hallowed halls of your house are even more exciting!
Why? Because now there's a second floor, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But before you bash your way in, I've got a trifling task for you to tackle.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Capricious Mithra cubs have cajoled critical information out of the M.H.M.U., and I want you to wrest it from them!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Visit the three nations and question them, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Now you know the nitty-gritty, so enjoy your new floor, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Kupopo? You mean you already know?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Magnificent and marvelous! Then proceed without delay!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Enjoy extra space to store your sundries!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Remodel your room to fit your finicky tastes!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Incorporate ostentatious overseas objects! All this and more!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But only on the second floor, kupo. I like the first floor as it is.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And as for your potted plants--they only persevere on the ground, kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And moghancement effects only activate for furnishings fitted to the first floor.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Wish we could help more, but we spend enormous amounts of energy on one floor already!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Go forth and frolic in your new abode, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can access the antechambers from the front door. Enjoy!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 80) 1≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻%ｃ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ might bring a certain je ne sais quoi to your Mog House, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What's this, then?
Someone gave you this envelope, did they?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Wh-what is this!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
This rubbish does not fool me!
I know a forgery when I see one.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Most unpleasant.
Do not speak to me of this matter again!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You called for me, Your Majesty?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Francmage?
I was not expecting you so soon. Monarlais...tell him.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Yes, sire.≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Francmage, I've summoned you here today to talk about one thing--the Northlands investigation.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, yes, that. Those Bastoker Humes are causing no end of trouble--saying they want to investigate here, there, and the other place...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It is true! The Humes are fools, and no better. Can they truly believe that some ancient power lies hidden in that forsaken wasteland?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Hah! Do they hope to find the gates to eternal Paradise there, in that lair of fiends most uncouth? Preposterous!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We must take control of this situation immediately. Still, we cannot let them walk about the Northlands freely. Who knows what they're plotting under the guise of this “investigation.”≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Francmage, listen. Go with the investigation party, and keep a close eye on what our foreign “friends” do. They are up to something, it is certain.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I am sure nothing will come of this, but in case they do find something in that wasteland, do not let them take it. Understood?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As you command, my lord. I would give the very blood that runs in my veins if it were to further the cause of our kingdom. You can rely on me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: These foreigners are wily and faithless. Never let down your guard, and may the Goddess of the Dawn protect you in Her mercy.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The king has taken a beautiful queen, and I think a splendid addition to the royal family is not far off. An heir, perhaps...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We people of San d'Oria, too, must ever look to the future. The Elvaan must never fall behind foreigners, in power or faith.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I understand, Your Grace.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Very good. Do well, Francmage.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Yes, sire! My life for the Kingdom!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
As I thought, there is nothing here...
Only barren wastelands as far as the eye can see.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
But there is something wrong about this place, I can feel it.
I don't think-wink we should leave Xarcabard yet.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I agree. My nose has never failed me, but I don't smell anything. That's not normal.
Something really terrrible must've happened here a long time ago.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Ridiculous. We cannot base our decisions on your feelings alone.
You can stay and look for whatever “terrible thing” is supposed to be here, but I--≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Help! Come quick!
Raogrimm and Cornelia, they--≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ulrich? What happened!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We were attacked by fiends, and Raogrimm and Cornelia fell down a crevice...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, no! Oh, no!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Grr! Where!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: This way!≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 34) 3≻≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Raogrimm and Cornelia...where could they have gone?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We have to assume the worrrst. If I can't find them, no one can.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Why must Humes and Galka be so irresponsible!?
It is their fault for wandering off without telling us!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
There are too few of us left to continue. I say we go back.
Besides, we would find nothing even if we stayed.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I second that.
I've had enough of this crrreepy place anyway.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: B-but, there are still places we haven't looked--≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
We have seen enough.
There is nothing here but dust and ruins.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We accomplished nothing but losing two members of our party and wasting an extraordinary amount of time...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Yeah, you're right.
This whole expedition was a failure. Let's head back tomorrow.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Ulrich.
Tell me something... Was it really an accident?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What do you mean?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Is it not true that there is some...shall we say, tension, between Humes and Galka in Bastok these days?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Are you accusing me of something, Elvaan?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Hah! Calm down. I do not care if it was an accident or not. I care even less about your little country's problems.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Just...do not cause any more trouble with such trivial matters while I am around.
That is all.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
It is quite late to be up and about, Sir Francmage.
Is something wrong?≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 34) 4≻≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Ah, Courisaille.
It's nothing. I could not sleep, so I decided to take a walk.
Leave me; I am fine.≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 34) 4≻≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Yes, sir.≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 34) 4≻≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
No! Not you...?
Raogrimm? What do you mean!?
He died in an accident! I know nothing!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Sir Francmage?
Are you all right, sir?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Stop! Do not come any further!
No, nooo--≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
...
S-Sir...Francmage?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The hunt registry is a tome through which seasoned adventurers can undertake assignments to eliminate monsters deemed to be impediments to A.M.A.N. activities.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The hunt registry is a tome through which veteran soldiers can undertake assignments to eliminate monsters deemed to be impediments to S.M.A.N. activities.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Assignments, or “hunts,” can be undertaken simply by selecting the name of a monster listed in the registry.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Pertinent information such as monster elusiveness and ferocity has been recorded for your reference.
As safety cannot be guaranteed, we ask that you hunt within your ability.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Hunts pit you against creatures of extreme ferocity, and are not intended for training.
For this reason, you cannot undertake a hunt while a training regime is active.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Should party members undertaking a common hunt defeat the objective, the kill will be considered valid for all.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Upon the completion of a hunt, record your success in a hunt registry.
Doing so will earn you rewards corresponding to difficulty as well as “scylds”--tokens of your valor.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
More scylds will grant you access to increasingly difficult and rewarding assignments.
Be warned, however, that once expended, scylds will not be refunded for any reason.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Lastly, please note that a mandatory cool-down period will be imposed upon all hunters following the completion of a hunt. Until this time has elapsed, you will not be permitted to undertake another hunt.≺Prompt≻

field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: He is a man of many talents. It would be wise to seek his acquaintance. Good luck!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Excellent work. How fares the archduke?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: He wants you to gather the magicite? I know nothing about objects of lore, but perhaps you should try learning more about Davoi, Beadeaux, and Castle Oztroja.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: At ease, soldier. So, how was the archduke?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: He wants you to gather magicite? That kind of thing is far beyond my expertise, so you should scour the land for clues on Davoi, Beadeaux, and Castle Oztroja.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: So, you saw the archduke... Well, how did it go?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: He wants you to gather magicite? I can't offer any advice on those. Maybe you can try learning about Davoi, Beadeaux, and Castle Oztroja...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Magicite! Yes, these stones emit the same power as crystals. Though impure, that power is great indeed.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Now it is clear why the beastmen gathered where they did. They were drawn to the magicite's great power!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Yes, it is time to eradicate the beastman threat once and for all.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I thank you for your service. Here is ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻6ｇ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻. With it, you may travel to any nation you please.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: For now, I thank you for your service. Since you already have ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻6ｇ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻, please accept this instead. May you spend it wisely.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The three stones are incomplete, but with the powers of the fourth stone that rests deep beneath Castle Zvahl...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Perhaps then the Shadow Lord will rise again.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Of course, the talisman that seals Zvahl's inner depths was put in place over twenty years ago. It would stop any attempt.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I've also read that the three keys to open the seal were kept safely by the three great nations...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Your Grace!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What is it?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Dire news, Your Grace! The leaders of all three nations have been attacked!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Attacked... By beastmen?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Yes, Your Grace.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Confound them! They're one step ahead of us.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: So, they seek to resurrect the Shadow Lord... Quite a lofty goal for beastmen.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: So be it, then. Perhaps you should return to your embassy.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I will call for your aid again soon. Until then, be well.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Hey, what's going on? Oh, you don't have to tell me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, so you went to Castle Oztroja and met a girl named Verena there.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And she gets along with the beastmen. Wow, so maybe we could get along.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Hey, Wolfgang! Wolfie, you here?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What would you ask of me, Lord Eald'narche?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Could you find someone named Verena and bring her here? I heard she's Aldo's little sister.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Of course, my lord. But may I ask why? She seems of...questionable intentions.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I think she has some nifty powers, so I just want to play with her. That's all.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, and don't tell this to Kam'lanaut. I want to surprise him.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As you wish, my lord.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Heh. I can't wait!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: ≺Player Name≻! At long last you return! Congratulations on your success!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I regret you have no time for reprieve. Our beloved San d'Oria is in danger!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Her Excellency is away, so please take this to the court in her stead. Take the airship! I will remain and do what I can.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Make haste to San d'Oria! You can board the airship now, can you not? I will remain here and find out what I can.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, I am relieved there was no danger. Our embassy is safe as well. For now, obey the court's commands.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: ≺Player Name≻! You made it back in one piece!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: The ambassador's away, so you'll have to carry this back to the administration. Take the airship! I'll stay here to get to the bottom of this.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Get on that airship to Bastok, soldier! I'll stay here and find out what I can.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: So, it's business as usual in Bastok, huh? Well, we have nothing special for you here, so try following the administration's directives.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: There you are! Great work, ≺Player Name≻!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: I'm sorry, but you've got no time to rest! Our beloved Windurst is in grave danger!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: With the ambassador away, I want you to take this back to the motherland. Take the airship; it's faster. I'll find out what I can here.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Hurry-scurry! Take the airship back to Windurst! I'll find out what I can here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As long as the Star Sibyl is safe, then all is well. We don't have any tasks for you here, so continue your service to your country.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Stand down!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Thank you. If the sovereign requests your audience, access to the chamber will be granted by the guards inside.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I'm sorry, but you will need ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻6ｇ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ to get in.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: This the hall of the Ducal Guards. Only the finest warriors may join. Come to think of it, this is no place for civilians like you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Sir Wolfgang is our leader. He was selected not just for his skill at arms, but also for his unwavering determination.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Who are you and what's your business!? Oh, you're an attaché... My apologies! I have to check everyone who passes through here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In this job, I assume everyone's guilty until proven innocent. I meant no offense.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Welcome. This is the home of the archduke, so please conduct yourself accordingly.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Lords Kam'lanaut and Eald'narche rarely make public appearances.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And you need a special permit just to have an audience with them.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Both have kept their youth through all these years. Perhaps some otherworldly power watches over them. Great prophets like them are few indeed!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Say... You know Aldo, the guy who runs the organization called the Tenshodo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Do you know him?
≺Selection Dialog≻Yes.
No.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The Tenshodo was founded by Aldo's father. They've done so well in trading abroad that they own the black market in these parts. Er, so I've heard...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Aldo took over after his father died. I've heard all kinds of things about him, but they say he's a smart and honorable man.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, you're a Tenshodo member? I guess you know more than I do, then.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You should do business with the Tenshodo, too. They supply us with hard-to-find goods now and then.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Beyond us stands the peace monument, constructed after the war. The embassies were built around it.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Lords Kam'lanaut and Eald'narche designed these gardens of Ru'Lude. One look is enough to see how much they treasure peace.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: These grounds are the domain of Lords Kam'lanaut and Eald'narche. Please conduct yourself properly.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Have you ever met Lord Eald'narche? He's still a lad, but the archduke's brother is gifted with incredible talents.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Jeuno is safe as long as it has Archduke Kam'lanaut and Lord Eald'narche.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The three great nations preach friendship, but beneath the facade is a struggle for supremacy. Nobody can tell what will come of it.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: That is why we must focus on our duties. There is no guarantee that the reign of peace we enjoy now will last.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Did you know that Lord Eald'narche wears an eye patch? He had an accident when he was little, but it hasn't fazed him! Bless his heart.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In the chaos of war, the archduke had a brilliant plan. He believed that the three nations' only chance was to cast aside their squabbles and stand as one.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Each nation had to shoulder an equal burden in the struggle against the beastmen. His strategy was truly brilliant!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Without his guidance, this world would have turned to shadow under the domination of the beastmen.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In the past, there was a terrible war. My father once told me how the earth, swept by furious winds, was soaked in the blood of the fallen.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I heard his tales every time he drowned his sorrows in drink. Now his stories are etched in my mind.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Sir Wolfgang's father was a famous soldier, too. He commanded Jeuno's forces in the Crystal War, and his exploits are legendary.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: After the war, he looked after the families of his fallen comrades. What a great man... There's more to being a soldier than just brute strength!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Sometimes I see the darndest things here. One time, a rookie of ours got cursed in the necropolis of Eldieme, and I didn't know what to do.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I bet things are brewing that are way too crazy for us to imagine.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Once I took a new guy to the Eldieme Necropolis, and he got cursed there. He went berserk, and had this unstoppable craving for raw meat.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, I gave it some thought... And you know those torches in the rooms made of stone? Well, I heard that spirits hate them...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
So, I figured it might help if I lit a lantern with those flames and brought it here.
That's how we saved the guy.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But, uh... I've also heard that some spirits actually like that kind of fire. So, it might not always be such a good idea.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I guess we were lucky then. We had no idea what else to do, and just wanted to do what we could.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you want, we can lend you the lantern we used back then. What do you say?≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
Do you want to borrow the lantern?
≺Selection Dialog≻Yes, please.
Not now.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Try and bring back the flames in this lantern. We don't know what else could help.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I seem to remember there were four torches, and that you had to light them in the proper order.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Yeah, that's right. I remember screwing that up. Too bad I forgot the real order, though. Well, I'm sure you can figure it out.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Don't forget it's the stone-wrought room that you're after. The torches in the caverns are for something else, so don't mix them up.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, yeah? Well, you're free to use it any time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you knew exactly which spirit is doing the possessing, then you can figure out how to exorcise it. But that's the last resort, you know?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, the flame thing didn't work, huh? Well, I'm just glad the spirit's gone!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Yep, I knew it. You learn something every day. I'm gonna write this up in the Guardsman's Daily.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: I always wondered how someone of his height lit that lantern.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The archduke hosts so many dignitaries, every night is a banquet. Composing original menus makes me fret!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: This is the archduke's chamber. Only here can he find refuge from his busy schedule...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But he's always out, doing his best for the Duchy. We all look up to him so much. His deeds benefit not only Jeuno, but the entire world as well.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: All I can do in return is change his sheets and prepare hot soup.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: These works are part of Lord Eald'narche's collection. His Lordship is versed in history as well as art.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The archduke and his brother often relax in this room. We always wait outside, but they do seem to get along quite well.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I do not pry into their conversations, but their knowledge of politics, culture, and philosophy rivals that of scholars.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Our job is to confront anyone suspicious. Why, if anything happened to the archduke, the repercussions would be felt around the world.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: This monument was built at the end of the war...as a reminder that nobody should suffer like that ever again.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And now, people forget the mistakes of the past and quarrel all over again. I bet this is the only place where that promise is still remembered.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I want somebody to take this map I got in the north and stave off impending disaster, but you don't look ready for such a task.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: The reward is really something. It's a key the archduke himself found in the ruins. They say it makes things...automatically. Well? Wanna try it?≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: We stand in the gardens of Ru'Lude, at the very top of Jeuno's superstructure.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: A mighty fine palace, this is. Why, it's like a castle in the clouds! I'm so glad I came all this way to see it.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Oh, now where'd the wife head off to? I suppose she'll show up if I stay put here.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: I wonder how they managed to build this place? Jeuno's full of mysteries, like the airships! But the biggest one of all is the archduke. Nobody knows who he is or where he's from.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
Welcome to the auction house.
Do you have any questions about our establishment?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What do you want to know?
≺Selection Dialog≻What is the auction house?
How are auctions run?
Are there any fees?
Are there any limits?
How do you check up on merchandise?
How do you remove an item?
My “Sales Status” list is full!
Nothing right now.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Auction houses can be found in all of Vana'diel's major cities. Here adventurers gather to bid on battle spoils, unwanted items, old armor...almost anything.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Currently, the auction houses in Bastok, San d'Oria, Windurst, and Jeuno all work independently. Therefore, prices differ from city to city.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Adventurers may use any auction house regardless of nationality.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The first adventurer to bid at or above the asking price will automatically purchase the product.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Once put up for auction, merchandise will remain there for a maximum of thirty weeks Vana'diel time (nine-and-a-half days Earth time).≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If merchandise does not sell within this time limit, it will be returned to the seller's current residence.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Transaction fees are proportional to the amount for which an item is put up on auction. The method of calculating this fee is different for single items and stackable items.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: A transaction fee is collected when any merchandise is put up for auction. This fee is nonrefundable.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The International Auction House Committee, or IAHC, has declared that a maximum of seven items may be put up for auction at one time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, the IAHC has recently removed the limit to how many items one may purchase.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: A small amount of time is required before new merchandise appears on our bid list.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Once an item appears on your “Sales Status” list, it may not immediately appear on the bid list. If you do not see your item on the bid list, try looking again at a later time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you would like to withdraw an item from an auction, you must travel to the auction house, and select “Stop Sale” from the “Sales Status” menu.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: To remove an item from your “Sales Status” list, you must visit an auction counter to acknowledge the sale or return of your merchandise.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Otherwise, previously sold or returned items will fill up your list and prevent you from selling any more merchandise.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: At any auction counter, open the “Sales Status” menu and acknowledge the transaction to clear it from the list.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Press the confirm button to remove any transaction colored yellow (sold) or red (returned).≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Is there anything else you would like to know?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In the past, many have amassed great wealth through the auction house. I hope you find fortune, too!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It's kind of hard to believe, but did you know that Jeuno was once a run-down, tiny little fishing village?≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Long ago, there was a young man--captain of a fishing boat, he was--who lived a modest life in the peaceful harbors of Jeuno. It was often hard for him to make ends meet, but he and his fishing buddies had no complaints. They loved their tiny village...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, one stormy night, fate came knocking at his door when he rescued two strange lads from the nearby waters. From that day on, the wheels of change began to turn.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There was something different--something special--about those two. They possessed a great deal of knowledge and leadership, and in just a short period of time, they transformed Jeuno from an insignificant dot on the map into a giant metropolis.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: At first, the captain welcomed these changes with open arms. However, later he began to ask himself if all this was truly for the good of Jeuno, or if the city was just being used as a piece of some bigger plan put into motion by the two mysterious men...≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: The WES (World Emigration Service) is currently taking applications for those who wish to immigrate to another World.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: When applying, please note the following:≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can always cancel your emigration during the application period by talking to any of the WES agents located conveniently about Vana'diel. However, once the period is over, you will no longer be able to cancel.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: After immigrating to another World, you will not be allowed to return to your previous World. Also, emigration is only allowed during periods when the WES is accepting applications.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You will be unable to choose the World to which you wish to emigrate. For more information on Worlds that we are accepting emigration applications for, please check the current PlayOnline news.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If your character happens to have the same name as another player in the World to which you emigrate, you will have to change your name before entering that World.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Emigration of characters is done one at a time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you request emigration for any of your other characters, please conduct all applications separately.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: All items up for auction and in your Delivery Box will be lost when you emigrate. Please collect these items before moving.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Any items in your Mog Safe will be transported with you to the new World.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ah, standing here in Jeuno brings back memories...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Twenty years ago, I worked in this very town with scientists from all over the world. We were trying to solve the hunger problem that plagued Vana'diel.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What? You want to hear about what happened twenty years ago?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Twenty years ago, I worked in this very town with scientists from all over the world. We were trying to solve the hunger problem that plagued Vana'diel.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Koru-Moru! Now that's a name that brings back memories.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: People say that we scientists are a strange bunch, but Koru-Moru...now he was a crazy one.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But even a weird one like him had a girl he loved. I'll never forget seeing him and Rasusu...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You say you're looking for Rasusu? Now why would a young ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[lad/lass] like yourself want to do that?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I see. Koru-Moru's finally started to remember... Well, that's one box of memories that should remain shut.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you promise to keep quiet on the subject, I'll tell you what I know.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Twenty years ago, the Rolanberry Fields were rampaged by those dreadful Crawlers. The problem escalated to the point where the people of Jeuno had nothing to put on their dinner tables.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: One adventurer saw the problem that lay before Jeuno and began calling for volunteers to travel to the Crawlers' Nest and exterminate the queen.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Seeing that her research was going nowhere, Rasusu decided to take her chances and go along with the adventurer.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I tried to contact Koru-Moru, in hopes that I could get him to persuade Rasusu to stay in Jeuno. But at the same time, Windurst had its own problems, and I couldn't get ahold of him.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And then she went...and no one ever saw her again.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: After the war ended, I tried writing Koru-Moru many times, but I could never bring myself to tell him the truth about his beloved Rasusu.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Windurst had been devastated by the Great War, and Koru-Moru had seen the devastation with his own eyes. I could not bear to be the bringer of any more tragic news.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Knowing Koru-Moru, the memories of Rasusu probably got lost in the back of his tiny little head...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You know Koru-Moru, so you can understand why I ask you to keep the truth from him--for his sake.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Twenty years ago, Koru-Moru and Rasusu worked side by side for the good of Vana'diel.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, the terrible Crawlers pulled the young lovers apart. A sad, sad story, it is.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What is this you have found? ≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 80) 1≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻ ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻$ａ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻? Where did you get that?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You say that this belonged to Rasusu?
Then it is true. The poor soul perished in that infernal place...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

I do commend you for your effort. May you succeed next time.≺Prompt≻

≺Selection Dialog≻Nothing.

Conquest results.
Donating crystals.

The effects of controlling regions.

Regions under beastman control.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: All three nations are striving daily to put more regions under their control. This is what we call “conquests.” You can take part in it and serve your country by defeating enemies while you have Signet cast on you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Each region comprises several areas, and the nation that rids those areas of the most monsters gains control of the region.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Nations receive goods and resources from regions under their control.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: So, the more regions we control, the richer our nation becomes.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Border guards are also placed in outposts within regions under our control.
They are there to cast Signet on adventurers like yourself.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Once you have your nation's Signet, you will be able to acquire crystals from enemies you defeat.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Not only that, but you will also receive conquest points. You get more conquest points if you defeat enemies in regions that are not under your nation's control. These points can be used to purchase items from guards like myself.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
So you see...conquests benefit nations and adventurers alike.
We expect you to do your best to serve your country.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You can see the current state of conquests by selecting “Region Info” from the main menu.
Conquest results in all regions are regularly recalculated, so you may want to check them from time to time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Shops in our city will be selling different items according to our conquest rank.
The Troupe Valeriano will also visit the nation that finishes first and bring a little joy to its citizens.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You can donate crystals to your nation once you achieve rank 2.
Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
We would like you to donate crystals to your nation from now on.
Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You can acquire crystals by defeating enemies while you have your nation's Signet.
Having Signet cast on you is also the only way of taking part in conquests.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Rank points will be awarded to you for each crystal you donate, and you may be offered new missions as your rank goes up.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You also receive rank points for completing missions.
Complete missions and take part in conquests to raise your rank and serve your country.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You are awarded conquest points when you defeat monsters while you are taking part in conquests.
Select "Region Info" from the menu to check your current number of conquest points.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can purchase items from guards like myself with your conquest points, but be warned that the number of points you spend will be subtracted from your current total.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: When conquest results are announced, you will be told which country controls the region you are in at that time. Sometimes regions may become neutral, or beastmen may even gain control of regions.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If we gain control of a region, border guards will be placed at its outposts to help adventurers like you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Merchants will also be placed there, and goods from that region will find their way to the local shops here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Gaining control of regions is the basic principle behind conquests. We need each of you to do your best, and bring our nation to the top of the ranks.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Of course, sometimes we lose regions to other nations...so we must try to take them back before the next conquest results are announced.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As an incentive, we will award you with more conquest points for defeating monsters in those regions.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But if we are allied with another nation, you will only be awarded the regular rate for defeating monsters in our allies' regions. On the other hand, we will award you with more points for fighting in the top-ranked nation's regions.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Our paramount concern lies in the beastmen gaining control of our regions.
If too many of us are defeated in a region, the beastmen will gain control of it.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If this happens, not only is it a great blow to our pride, but you will be unable to acquire any crystals in that region.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The beastmen are a menace to all nations. If they rise to power, we must all unite and drive those vile creatures from that region.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We need you to bring supplies to the outpost border guards who are placed in regions under our control.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is one outpost in each region. Select “Region Info” from the menu, and look for the areas with a small flag mark on the map. That is where they are.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Here are the supplies. Just give them to the guard at the outpost and your mission will be complete.
Now, choose which outpost you want to go to. We give different rewards for each region, so choose carefully.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Welcome to the border shop! If you trade me unused equipment, I'll add their value to your country's region points!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
It should please you to know that I now also deal in ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻%≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻.
Bigger pieces will earn you more points for your nation, and I'll even toss some gil into the equation!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I see that your home country has control of this region. Feel free to browse through my wares.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I see that your home country is allies with the country in control of this region. Feel free to browse through my wares.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I can teleport you to your home country for ≺Numeric Parameter 1≻ gil or ≺Numeric Parameter 3≻ conquest ≺Singular/Plural Choice (Parameter 3)≻[point/points].≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Word has it that the entire set of mog tablets has been recovered. 
Oh, happy day! In honor of the occasion, I can teleport you to your home country free of charge.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I am terribly sorry, but it seems as if you do not have enough gil.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I am terribly sorry, but it seems as if you do not have enough conquest points.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, due to your home country's lack of influence in the region, this is the only transaction I am authorized to perform with you at the moment.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I am looking forward to doing business with you again in the future!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points by a small amount. If you have anything else, by all means, trade them to me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points moderately. If you have anything else, by all means, trade them to me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points greatly. If you have anything else, by all means, trade them to me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I could not accept one or more items you tried to trade me. Please remove those items and try again.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Sorry. I can only take certain types of weapons, shields, or armor.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Thank you. This will increase your nation's region points ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 1)≻[by a small amount/moderately/greatly].
For this transaction I will also furnish you with ≺Numeric Parameter 0≻ gil.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: My apologies, but this type of item needs to be individually appraised. Please trade them to me one at a time.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
We are currently on a beastman-purging campaign. We support adventurers from all nations.
Do your best to rid the world of those vile creatures.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
We are currently conducting an international exchange campaign.
You may spend your conquest points to purchase items from foreign guards.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Thanks to you, our nation is now first in the conquest race!
Here is a small token of our appreciation.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Adventurers from nations that are ranked higher than ours in the conquest race may purchase items from us, but at a higher rate.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You cannot currently purchase this item.
Please choose another.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Currently our nation is dispatching Expeditionary Forces across Vana'diel, and requests the participation of brave adventurers such as yourself.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Requirements for participating in an E.F. are simple. Your party must consist of ≺Numeric Parameter 5≻ members. Each member must be from this country, rank 3 or higher, and have reached a sufficient level.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Once your party is ready, come to me and I will teleport you to the nearest outpost.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There, you will receive an insignia of the Expeditionary Force. When you succeed in taking control of the area, you can exchange the insignia for your reward.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Join the E.F. in ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 7)≻[Ronfaure/Zulkheim/Norvallen/Gustaberg/Derfland/Sarutabaruta/Kolshushu/Aragoneu/Fauregandi/Valdeaunia/Qufim/Li'Telor/Kuzotz/Vollbow/The Elshimo Lowlands/The Elshimo Uplands]?
≺Selection Dialog≻Join the E.F.
Not this time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Your party doesn't have enough members, or some of the members are not in this area. Gather all those who are participating and return here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: One of your party members is not a citizen of this country. We do not allow any foreign participants in the E.F.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: One of your party members has not achieved rank level 3. We cannot reveal any of our tactical strategies to those who have not shown their loyalty to our country.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: One of your party members is below level ≺Numeric Parameter 6≻. For the safety of the adventurer and those accompanying him or her, we cannot allow anyone below the limit to participate in the E.F.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I see that you are ready.
I grant you permission to join the current Expeditionary Force. When you are ready to teleport to the outpost, talk to me once more.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: This ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ is no longer valid. We will dispose of it here.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Your invalid ensignias have been disposed of.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Welcome back from the expedition. Our nation was successful in its campaign. Let me give you your reward.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You received ≺Numeric Parameter 1≻ conquest points!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: When participating in an Expeditionary Force, concentrate your efforts on fighting foes that give you the most experience points. And don't forget to confiscate the contents of any beastman treasure chest you happen to come upon.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I will now hand you your insignia. Be sure to read the inscription on the back before you begin your duties.
Once Signet has been bestowed upon you, prepare to be teleported.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You could not be teleported. Ask me again, please.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The conquest results are currently being tallied. Come back later.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You have received permission to join the Expeditionary Forces!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Currently we rank first in Vana'diel's conquest, but that must not be taken for granted. We must continue our fight to remain on top.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We had first place in our hands, but we let it slip away. If we want to be ranked first in Vana'diel, each and every one of us must do their part. I look forward to hearing of your achievements.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Our country has fallen to third in the conquest of Vana'diel. We must step up our efforts to improve the situation.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You must fight in battles that gain high levels of experience. This is the only way we can bring areas under our country's control.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Currently, our country is the dominant force in this region. If we can maintain this level, control of this area will be ours.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Currently, our country is a major force in this region. However, we cannot take this for granted. If we let down our guard, we will surely lose control of the area!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Currently, our country has only minor influence in this region. We're counting on you to get us out of this hole we've dug ourselves into.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Currently, our country's influence in this area is minimal. If we do not act quickly, control of this region will certainly be taken by a rival country.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Take care when passing through, as this area is currently overrun with beastmen! Something must be done, or the enemy will have control of the entire region.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I should cut you up and send you to Heavens Tower! Gawk! Gawk!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
Kahk! Silence...
Our little friend came all the way from Windurst to greet us. Let us hear what he has to say.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Kahk-ka-ka! You came all this way to ask about the Full Moon Fountain?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, you Tartutaru have probably already realized why the Horutoto Ruins were built and why the Full Moon Fountain exists underneath them.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Those ruins are evil.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The towers sponge dry the areas around Sarutabaruta of all their magic.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You think that we Yagudo are the cause of these wastelands, but you only have yourselves to thank. You--the Tarutaru that activated those towers!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The towers are all damaged! How do you explain magic still being drained from the plains of Sarutabaruta?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What about you Yagudo? What are those things that you continue digging? Those stones...maybe they are the cause of all this?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Kahk-ka-ka...I commend you on your perceptiveness.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But the reason Sarutabaruta is becoming a wasteland has nothing to do with those stones.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: That night, twenty years ago, when we were defeated by your armies, you made a grave mistake...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Kahk! Kahk! You still do not understand?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Make your way deep into the central tower of the Horutoto Ruins. There you will see first hand what the Star Sibyl and those summoners really did.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The moon and the stars no longer smile upon Windurst. Now, the world shall kneel before the Yagudo!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
<Sigh>
Well, it has been thirty years. Just look at me. I'm not as young as I used to be.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ah, those were the days...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What's this? You want to know what would impress the bushin? Hmmm...
Well, when I was still his disciple, I once presented him with ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻ ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻$ｅ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
He was so pleased that he didn't just let me see the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻#≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻, he let me try it on!
I could feel the weight of the souls of all the bushin that had worn it before me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But that weight was too great for me, and ever since that day, I've been striving to improve my skills.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But even now I don't think I could even grasp that belt with my own hands, let alone tie it around my waist. I still have much to learn...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
...
How many rounds have we gone now, ≺Player Name≻...?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I remember every single blow, every tiny shift of your stance.
I can't tell you how much I look forward to our little matches, heh heh heh.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But you know, I never imagined anyone would conquer all the challenges I set before ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[him/her]. Goes to show that even old Maat can be taught a thing or two!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Now, I can't let such a great hero go home empty-handed.
I've decided to grant you any one wish you ask of me.
Don't get too exotic, though. I'm just an old man, not some Far Eastern genie!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Come on, then. No need to be shy.
What's it to be?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
...!
Take off my hat!?
Are you sure that's want you want? Not much exciting going on under an old man's cap!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It's not too late to change your mind, you know.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There must be something else you want. A lifetime supply of Goblin chocolate? Afternoon tea with Princess Claidie? ≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 80) 1≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻ ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻$≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻, perhaps? Or maybe ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻ ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻$ａ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
No? You've made up your mind, it seems.
Young people these days--no imagination.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
But if that's what you really want, it makes things easy for me, I suppose.
I'll give you one last chance to change your wish...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, alrighty then.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Are you ready?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Try not to blink...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Heh heh heh.
Are you happy now? Bet you're thinking you should've changed your mind when you had the chance, huh?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Aw, don't look so disappointed, ≺Player Name≻. You think I'd let you walk away with nothing but an eyeful of my wrinkled noggin?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Even the mightiest oak will wither with the passing of time. Its vibrant leaves will fade to brown, and crumble into dust. I, too, will one day have to leave this garden behind for good.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Do you understand what I'm trying to say?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
When that time comes, I want you to take up this cap and become the mighty oak. Watch over the saplings as they reach towards the sky.
I know you're up to the task, ≺Player Name≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Do I have your word?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, that takes a load off my mind.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I've got plenty of spark left in me, though, so don't go getting ahead of yourself!
I'll be around whenever you're ready for another bout. Heh heh heh!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: No one is allowed to meet with the archduke or the ducal scientists unless it absolutely necessary.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The officials have been extremely busy making arrangements for numerous expeditionary forces to be sent to various locations around Quon and Mindartia.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you have any business with the archduke or the ducal scientists, please leave your message with us and we will relay it to the proper authorities.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, we cannot guarantee that you will receive a hasty reply.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is a man from the Alchemists' Guild who has been waiting to speak with the scientists for a number of days.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I believe he is still waiting somewhere near the archduke's quarters. Pour soul...≺Prompt≻
