field.Element:Text: So that's why Captain Wolfgang has been on edge lately... But what is really going on at those crags?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I see you have begun to show some interest in the strange occurrences that have been taking place in the past few weeks.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Let me tell you a little of what I have heard...
Recently, the Duchy has been abuzz with strange tales of travelers being drawn into strange whirlpools located in the Valkurm Dunes and on Qufim Island...and never coming back.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: From what I gather, the ducal scientists believe this phenomenon has something to do with the shattered Telepoints at the Crags of Holla, Dem, and Mea.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: To collect data, a group of Ducal Guards is to be dispatched any day.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Strange whirlpools in Valkurm and Qufim...
Shattered Telepoints...
What could it all mean?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The investigatory report written by the Ducal Guards mentioned that the whirlpools in Valkurm and Qufim are made up of an unknown substance that they call the “Emptiness.”≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
And now there are rumors stating that by jumping into these dark vortexes, people can instantly teleport themselves to the lost island of Tavnazia!
I don't know about you, but I am staying right here where it is safe!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I've heard rumors that a bright light shot out of the sea somewhere to the north of Delkfutt's Tower.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: An investigatory party is scheduled to search the area for clues, but they'll have their work cut out for them. The currents in the Sea of Shu'Meyo are unpredictable and violent. Many a captain has lost his ship in those waters.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Did you know there is a mysterious group of officials in Jeuno known as the “Armathrwn Society”?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The last time I tried telling some of the new recruits about the group, Captain Wolfgang put me on latrine duty for nine and a half weeks!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You, a scruffy adventurer, spoke with Sir Nag'molada!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Did you know that he was a high-ranking member of the prestigious Armathrwn Society--the advisors to Archduke Kam'lanaut?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Sir Nag'molada often speaks with common people of the Duchy. I even heard that promotions are granted to those who happen to impress him.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I wonder if he will ever stop to speak with me... What would I say?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You're an adventurer, right? So you've probably already heard about the humongous dragon that flew over the western skies.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: At first everybody thought it might be a stray wyvern, but there are rumors that it was actually one of those ancient “wyrms”!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You want to know about the hooded officials in black robes that sometimes appear in the courtyard?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: They are all members of the Armathrwn Society--scientists working for the Duchy. I have heard that there are even quite a few female members.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: While the Jeuno Armada is making preparations for battle, it remains the duty of the Ducal Guard to ensure the safety of the citizens of Jeuno.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Did you hear that a super-secret weapon was being loaded onto one of the warships? I wonder what it could be...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Yes, I overheard some of the other guards mention that the society's scientists had built a terrifying new battle machine.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Alright! After using that contraption, along with the airships' ultra-powerful mammoth cannons, there won't be enough left of those wyrms to even make dragon burgers!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The Jeuno Armada is readying for an attack on the Wyrmking, Bahamut. However, there is nothing to worry about. Our forces are the strongest, most advanced in all Vana'diel.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Have you seen a strange-looking boy or girl running about the gardens?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you have, inform one of the Ducal Guards. There are currently warrrrants out for both of their arrrrests.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Their capture is crucial to the safety of not just Jeuno, but of all Vana'diel.
You and your fellow adventurers' assistance in the matter is greatly appreciated.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Members of the Armathrwn Society are to accompany the armada on its mission.
It is said that the society's technological advancements are what built this city and made it what it is today.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Lady Esha'ntarl is supposedly leading the mission against Bahamut. With such a skilled commander at the armada's helm, there isn't anything in Vana'diel that can stop the Duchy!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I know you may consider your nation a powerful force in Vana'diel, but Jeuno is the only nation with the resources to defeat the Wyrmking. Don't you forget it.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
One of the armada warships is missing!
With all the tightened security, how could anyone have pulled off a feat as grand as stealing an airship!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: While the Jeuno Armada is conducting its mission in the skies, it remains the duty of the Ducal Guard to ensure the safety of the citizens of Jeuno.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Did you find out anything more about the super-secret weapon the armada took with them?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: No... However, I did hear that the device dealt a severe blow to the mighty Wyrmking during the assault.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Wowzie! If I had an ultra-spiffy contraption like that, I'd be eating roast dragon burgers every night!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The latest reports state the recent armada mission was a success. However, it did not completely stop the Wyrmking and his minions. It is rumored that the fleet will launch its second attack once the current repairs on the warships are completed.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you have any information on the whereabouts of the girl the Duchy was searching for, I am sorry, but the warrant for her arrest has been dropped.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The Ducal Guard recently received news of her death...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Even with the technology of the Armathrwn Society on our side, the armada was unable to completely defeat the Wyrmking and his army. Perhaps we underestimated their power...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In its first wave of attacks, the armada was successful in dealing a large amount of damage to Bahamut. The Wyrmking will not stand a chance against the second wave.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
<Sigh>
I requested a transfer from the Ducal Guard to the armada crew, but I was turned down...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Why do I have to stand around the gardens while everyone else is having all the fun? Look at these biceps! I could take out a wyrm with one blow!
Well...maybe two blows.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We were beginning to wonder when you would arrive, ≺Player Name≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The duke vicarious is meeting a messenger from the East as we speak. When she is finished, you shall be next. Until then, you shall be kept in custody.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I apologize for the absence of Grand Duke Kam'lanaut. I, Esha'ntarl, shall serve in his stead.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I hear that you have come from the Eastern Empire to ask something of our nation. State your name and your request.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ...I am Tenzen. Born and raised in the Far East, I serve as a samurai under the mighty dynasty.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Lady Esha'ntarl, may I ask why my audience was not met by the duke himself?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 1)≻[Since the revival of the Shadow Lord/Even after the defeat of the Shadow Lord], the grand duke has been overwhelmed with his duties to the people of this land.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, you need not worry. I will take the responsibility of relaying your words directly to Lord Kam'lanaut.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: These two shall be witness to that.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: While short, my message is not a simple one. It is critical that the duke fully understands the grave nature of the situation that lies before us.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What I am about to say does not only affect my homeland, but the countries to the south and west, as well as this fair land.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The Emptiness is closing in.
It has already appeared in the far reaches of the Eastern Empire. I can assume that the same is true of the outlying areas in the southern and western lands.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The phenomenon started small, but in recent months it has begun to grow. Like sap oozes slowly from a tree, the Emptiness spreads across my country, swallowing whole the hills and forests.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
As it approaches, the children begin to dream.
When it arrives, it is not long before the adults, too, begin to dream.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The dream is always the same...
It tells us...the Keeper of the Apocalypse will soon appear, and bring with him the end of Vana'diel.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The Keeper of the Apocalypse...
A frightening name, is it not?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Your report of this “darkness”--this Emptiness--it is not news to us. In recent weeks, there have been reports of similar phenomena occurring in the areas around Jeuno.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, these reports state that the Emptiness, as you call it, is localized. That is why we have chosen to withhold this information from the public until it can be further researched. If it is true that the Emptiness has begun to spread, though, an immediate investigation may be necessary.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Shall the Duchy prepare a team?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
...
You...do not know why the Emptiness has appeared?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Unfortunately, our scientists have not yet come to any concrete conclusions. If your empire has any definite data, we would be delighted to hear it.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Are you suggesting that the cause of the Emptiness may be found in my land? Do not tell me that you are unaware that the five shards of legend rest here!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Do not tell me that you are unaware that it is the power of the five shards that protects Vana'diel from the Emptiness!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Tenzen of the East...
You are very straightforward with your accusations.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Let me see...
You feel that Jeuno is the cause of the Emptiness's growth.
You feel that our attempts to harness the power of the crystals have resulted in the spread of the darkness, am I correct?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, I am sorry to say that you are quite mistaken. Jeuno is fully aware of the power that the crystals radiate forth.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The five shards--the mothercrystals--are what support our world.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We, the Duchy, have taken it upon ourselves to inherit the will of the ancients and protect the Zilartian ruins and the crystals they hold.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We have kept this information from the nations of Bastok, Windurst, and San d'Oria to shield the mothercrystals from those who may wish to wrongly use their power for personal gain.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I see that the Eastern Empire has learned of the crystals' existence, and therefore we can no longer trust you, either.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Jeuno cannot allow the power of the mothercrystals to fall into the hands of those who may exploit it.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: My country's only wish is to prevent the Emptiness from taking away any more than it already has!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Seeing, with your own eyes, the darkness drain the life from your homeland... I can understand why you may not agree with our nation's stance.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Very well. I can tell you one thing.
The Duchy is currently in search of a boy. This boy is thought to be connected in some way to the Emptiness.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Even though he is not one of us, he has already found a way into three of the Zilartian ruins, the Emptiness following in his path.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We here believe that this boy is the Keeper of the Apocalypse of which you speak.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
A boy?
Could he be a messenger from another nation?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
That we do not know.
However...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Wolfgang.
Show the adventurer in.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
This adventurer was with the boy when he appeared near the mothercrystals.
≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[He/She] hails from the nation of ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[San d'Oria/Bastok/Windurst].≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[San d'Oria/The Republic/The Federation]!
What could ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[the king/the president/those mages] be conspiring!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Of course, ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[the Kingdom/Bastok/Windurst] has denied all ties to the boy.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As has this adventurer.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, if we learn that ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[San d'Oria/the Republic/the Federation] is behind this threat to the mothercrystals and the well-being of all those residing on Vana'diel...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Whether allies or not, Jeuno will be forced to take action against the nation. We will destroy them.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But this is still nothing more than speculation. If we had the time to conduct a proper investigation, it would be the first thing we did. Unfortunately, time is one luxury we do not have.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And that is why we must capture the boy immediately to learn of what he knows...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Exactly.
And that is why I offer you a chance--a chance to prove your country's true intents by joining this battle to save your nation--no, all of Vana'diel.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Adventurer.
Travel to the fourth crystal and wait for the boy. When he arrives, capture him and bring him here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Unlike the first three crystals, the fourth lies deep beneath Vana'diel's surface, somewhere below the glaciers of the Northlands.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Thirty years ago, an allied expedition visited the Northlands. If you could find one of the original members, you may be able to obtain some valuable information.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Francmage M Mistalle, of the Knights Mistalle in San d'Oria...
Iru-Kuiru, from the Rhinostery in Windurst...
Mythril Musketeer captain, Ulrich, from Bastok...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I have heard news that the criminal accused of destroying the Telepoints was captured and taken into custody.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, when questioned, ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[he/she] said she had nothing to do with the incidents. To prove ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[his/her] innocence, the Duchy has ordered the scoundrel to travel to the nations of Bastok, Windurst, and San d'Oria and gather information that will clear ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[his/her] name.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What is this? You say you have business with the captain?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Ah, ≺Player Name≻.
I was looking for you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Esha'ntarl, duke vicarious, would like to hear your account of what transpired in the Northlands.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
...?
What is this envelope?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
From Doctor Monberaux?
Why would he...?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
However, first things first.
Follow me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ah, welcome back, adventurer.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I see that you were unsuccessful in protecting the fourth crystal.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And now it is looking more and more like you are the one who is leading the boy...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Relax, adventurer. I am not blaming you for anything.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Nag'molada kept the secret of the amulet to himself.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It is his foolishness that acted as a catalyst for what occurred in the Northlands.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And now that we know the true identity of the boy, there is no reason to further suspect your nation's involvement. I apologize for not trusting you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, now we must put aside our misunderstandings and unite to save our world from being destroyed. Will you help us protect the mothercrystals?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Join forces with Jeuno?
≺Selection Dialog≻Yes.
No.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We have caused you much suffering, and I understand your anger. On behalf of the Duchy I ask for your forgiveness.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ≺Player Name≻...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In the presence of the fourth crystal, I have learned that a strange occurrence took place.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Is it true that the girl you took with you actually helped Selh'teus and thwarted the plans of our Nag'molada?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It is extremely important that you do not withhold information from us.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Is it true?
≺Selection Dialog≻Yes.
No.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I see...
The Duchy is currently searching for that girl.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We do not wish to punish her. We feel that she may be in grave danger. We must find her so we can protect her.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The first threat to her will be Nag'molada. He is already attempting to make it seem as if the fall of the fourth crystal was the girl's fault.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If he finds her, he will more than likely poison her mind, preventing her from speaking of anything that may harm his plan.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The second threat will be the boy, Selh'teus. His next destination will most surely be the fifth and final crystal.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, this crystal lies deep beneath the sea, and the only one who knows how to reach it is the girl.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Finally, the third threat will consist of assassins from the south.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You may have already heard the rumors of the Mithran sin hunters who have crossed the southern seas to try the theologians of Tavnazia.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: These hunters will not give up until they have punished all those they seek.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And that is why we need your help, ≺Player Name≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you find the girl, bring her here. No harm will be brought to her. I swear on the name of the Goddess.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Lady Esha'ntarl!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
≺Player Name≻.
Did you tell them everything that happened in the Northlands?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: My plan was flawless! If it wasn't for that despicable girl, Prishe, I would have captured Selh'teus, and this whole ordeal would be solved!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: That girl heard the whisper of Selh'teus's soul, sang the “Memoria de la S^tona,” and helped him escape!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The “testament of affinity” she possesses--it connects the hearts and souls of men. Selh'teus has been using that to control her!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But now we have the chance to find out his true intentions.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If we can capture the girl, we can use her to tap into Selh'teus's mind. We can learn if he truly arrived to save Al'Taieu!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You miserable man!
Are you saying Selh'teus does not know that our crusade ended long ago?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You fool!
Are you saying Selh'teus does not know that the celestial capital was destroyed long ago?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Perhaps it is we who do not know the true outcome of the crusade or the true fate of our capital!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I propose that an expedition be sent to Al'Taieu.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There we may find the answers to why Selh'teus survived all the centuries, and why he continues to poison the mothercrystals.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And that is why we must first investigate the line leading to the fifth crystal.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Please, grant me access to the Crystal Terminal!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
...
I understand why you feel an expedition to Al'Taieu is necessary.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[The Armathrwn Society/Kam'lanaut] has already made a decision on this matter. I seem to recall that you have been given orders to research the Moblin city that was discovered near Bastok.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: All affairs concerning Selh'teus have been left to Esha'ntarl. You are not to interfere.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But, Lady Esha'ntarl has been given the assignment of Bahamut.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Selh'teus is a much graver problem than you can imagine. I do not think...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Yes, you do not think!
Did you really believe attacking the boy with the Eye of Altana would defeat him!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Your impudence is the cause of all our troubles!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Nag'molada, do not misunderstand us. ≺Multiple Choice (Parameter 0)≻[The society does/Kam'lanaut does] not intend to pry at your faults.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The reason we have entrusted you with the Moblin investigation is because your excellent Kuluu powers of negotiation are vital for the success of the mission.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But Lady Esha'ntarl! You do not realize how powerful the boy has become...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Now with the Eye gone and the path to the fifth crystal sealed, how do you plan on dealing with him!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I don't think you even have a plan!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Very well, let me inform you of how we plan to stop Selh'teus.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
We can draw him forth without traveling to the fifth crystal.
We can seal him without your precious Eye of Altana.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: H-how...!?≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You can hear me, can you not...Selh'teus?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It is I who possess the other amulet you seek.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I am waiting, Selh'teus!
Come and fulfill the pact!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Here, take this envelope back to the doctor. It does not belong to me.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: But why would he try to...?≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Not but a few moments ago, Sir Nag'molada passed by this station. However, he did not seem himself. I wonder if something is wrong...≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: Even Captain Wolfgang has been looking disturbed since he received that envelope. What ever could be going on?≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: ≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 80) 1≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻%≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ and ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻%ａ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ cannot be used here.≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text:
≺Player Name≻...
Now that I have passed from the mortal realm, I have only you to turn to.
The time left to me is short.≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Thirty years ago, I came into contact with the insidious power of this land, and rose from the grave. However, at the same time, this world laid claim to a part of my soul...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I have been released from the hate that consumed me, but the half of my soul that was taken captive all those years ago is calling to me...
It has become a towering darkness. A raging hatred, spawned from the depths of my being...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Very soon I will be drawn into that soul. I no longer have the strength to resist. The soul that was divided will become whole once more, and that rage will take on physical form.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: A new Shadow Lord will be born. Surely you have sensed the growing evil? The beastman armies that are imprisoned here are massing for battle. They plan a return to the world of their origin, the realm that exists beneath the light of hope.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
My link to you will soon be severed, so listen carefully.
Thirty years ago, an expeditionary squad formed from the elite soldiers of each nation was sent to investigate the Northlands. You must have seen their memories when you first laid your hand upon the chunks of magicite.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Seek out the markings that the expedition members left behind. They will aid you in gaining entrance to this world.
You must defeat the Shadow Lord before our unification is complete.
My hopes go with you, ≺Player Name≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is an unusual arrangement of branches here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is an unusual arrangement of pebbles here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The strands of grass here have been tied together.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is an unusual arrangement of leaves on the ground.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I see you have met with Raogrimm.
His soul is no longer confined to that incarnation of rage, the Shadow Lord, yet the fact remains that he has committed sins beyond redemption.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In spite of those sins, I still wish to rescue him from the darkness. I no longer have a mortal body with which to act, and so the most I can do is guide you in my stead.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You will need the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻, a key that bridges the void between Vana'diel and that other world.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It is said that there are items in this world that gain a soul of their own through contact with the thoughts and dreams of other living creatures. The ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ is one of those items.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You must look for the Goblin peddlers. They are certain to have knowledge of the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻. When you have it safely within your grasp, seek out the markings that we left behind...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: That world is a land now draped in the blackest night. We can pass from one world to the other, but without the physical forms lost to us thirty years ago, there is little we can do to intervene.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Raogrimm is the one who... No, the world has been divided into separate realms through the machinations of the new Shadow Lord.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The Shadow Lord resides in the Xarcabard of the other reality. However, I fear you would be marching to your death should you go to confront him... I ask you to first obtain trophies from four of the alternate realms.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: We understand that there is little time to spare. But without a certain degree of power, it will be impossible to traverse the land the Shadow Lord holds in thrall. Show me your strength with the four trophies you bring back.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Those whose fate is linked to his world will empower the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ to guide you...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I never believed that my indifference to the state of other nations would cause harm to my beloved San d'Oria...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As part of my penance, I will infuse the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ with what guidance I can.≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I betrayed him...
And now I am needed, the one who cut down poor Cornelia. The man cursed with the brand of traitor...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Sure, I got everything I wanted, but what was left to me in the end? For one rash action, all I gained was an empty title and irreconcilable guilt...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I doubt you'll listen to the words of a traitor, but please, help free him from the bonds of his eternal night...≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Our expedition was supposed to have been an allied effortaru, but not one of us was interested in the fate of the other nations. In our hasty-waste to outdo each other, we failed to see to the heart of the mattaru.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Our attitudes led to the death of two of our members, and precipitated the birth of the Shadow Lord...
This sin does not belong on Raogrimm's shoulders alone. We all mustaru atone for our actions.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Please help him. Help Raogrimm escape from his horrid-worrid darkness, forever this time.≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Humes and Galka have never been the best of friends. I used to think that was just the way it was, and always would be.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I figured I'd be causing myself grrrief if I stuck my whiskers into other nations' problems. My next catnap was all that mattered to me in those days. Ignorrrance is bliss, as they say.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Responsibility for Raogrimm's trrransformation lies with all of us who traveled with him on that expedition. By sharing the blame for the crimes he committed as the Shadow Lord, we can finally call ourselves his trrrue companions.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Let me help you on your path. May guiding light fill this ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻!
Raogrimm's fate is in your hands.≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is a broken branch thrust into the ground here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is a symbol carved into the rock here.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I have been waiting for you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Do you remember the last words Raogrimm spoke to you? "The link will soon be severed"...
Do you understand the significance of these words?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
When the soul that was divided is whole once again, towering rage will take on physical form...
Yes, a new Shadow Lord will be born. Even I will no longer hear his voice.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Even now, I can barely feel the emanations of Raogrimm's faltering spirit. When those emanations fade completely, he will be...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The Xarcabard of that other realm is shrouded in a vast darkness, preventing contact from the outside. Even those of us without material bodies are unable to penetrate that mist of eternal night.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Until that mist clears, I cannot guide you to Xarcabard. 
The next place you must venture is the twin of Vana'diel's Beaucedine. There you will find the last trophy to complete the set of keys we need.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You must obtain the last trophy.
All five trophies combined with our power will create a synergistic force, allowing us to part the shroud for a few precious moments. It will open a path between worlds.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Take care, my brave adventurer.
May the blessings of Altana guide and protect you...≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Even after the blackest night, the golden sun always rises to begin a new morning.
This troubled land will soon have its dawn...of that I am certain.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I never thought to walk this land again, not even in death.
Is this what they call karma...?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
This land has borne the weight of my sins.
I will not beg for forgiveness, but accept my responsibility...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
So this is the reason for that unspeakable terror I feltaru here when I was still alive. It's possible that the other realm has existed for much longer than anyone ever dreamed...
Keep your wits aboutaru you, ≺Player Name≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I'm not rrreally fond of touching platitudes.
Snap Raogrimm to his senses with a big ol' smack to the head for me.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
It is time!
Put an end to this thirty-year nightmare, ≺Player Name≻.
≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 80) 1≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻! Show us the path to Xarcabard!≺Possible Special Code: 00≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Death does not exist in that realm. You might call it a “prison of souls.”≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Even those who fall in battle will rise again after a time as if nothing had happened.
Like a flame returning to a candle whose light has been extinguished...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It is an endless succession of life and death. How many times has that cycle repeated itself in that damned abode?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is one thing that bothers me. Whatever happened to the original wielders of the weapons and armor that the beastmen there now possess? If the statues in the shape of Orcs and such were once actual beastmen, then...? But I get carried away with my musings.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Please pay no mind to my ramblings.
You have secured the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻. An incredible feat. It proves the strength of your conviction, and is one of the keys you will need to enter Xarcabard.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You will need four such trophies.
Once you have them within your grasp, make your way to Beaucedine Glacier in the Northlands. Cornelia awaits you there.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I don't know about the other four, but I can't hear his voice anymore...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Is this another brand I must bear for my treachery? I must truly be hated if that's the case.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
It is something I would wish for at the moment, however. I pray this silence is just a continuation of our incompatible personalities.
If not, then it means his pronouncement has become reality...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 80) 1≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻.
This is more than just a testament to your strength. It is one of the keys that will lead you to Xarcabard, along with the trophies of the other realms.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
When you have all four trophies, travel to Beaucedine Glacier in the Northlands. You will find Cornelia waiting for you there.
That is all the wisdom I have left to give you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What is the true nature of that other world? I can only explain it as a place that lies beyond the limitarus of our knowledge.
But I'm sure I've feltaru that aura somewhere before...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: That's it. That protocrystal I came across when I was doing research in Elshimo. The magical emanations coming from the crystal gave me a similar impression. An avatar? No, that can'taru be...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Oh! Oh, I'm terribly-werribly sorry!
I appear to have driftarued into my old habits.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Now, ≺Player Name≻.
This ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ is both a symbol of your fortitude, and one of the keys that will help you gain access to Xarcabard. The trophies from the other three realms carry the same importance.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Gather all four trophies and hurry yourself on to Beaucedine Glacier. Cornelia will be waiting for you when you get there. But be wary, ≺Player Name≻. The blackness enveloping that world grows ever deeper, ever darker...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The beastmen of that world carry the spoils of prrrevious battles. Equipment that you or I would use.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I'm not able to touch them in my prrresent form, but I feel something about those weapons and armor...something extrrraordinary.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Wait, wait, wait!
I don't mean that they're currrsed or anything like that! It's something more like, um, not ominous, but...
How can I explain it?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Anyway! They're not evil, just...you know? Different from other normal swords and things. Being all ghostlike and stuff, you can feel things like that.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
But enough of that kinda talk--congrrratulations are in order!
You've got your paws on the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻! It shows you've got the goods in the hero department, and it will also help you get into Xarcabard.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But first you've got to collect the other three trophies and then hightail it to snowy Beaucedine Glacier. Cornelia should be up there waiting for you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 80) 1≻≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ and the four trophies.
These artifacts have long been lost to that other world. 
The Hydra Corps was a unit formed after our expedition to the Northlands.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
It must have been in the time of the Great War...
Nobody knows how the Hydra artifacts came to be there, but those five trophies will open the path for you.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Each of these items holds a measure of power. However, the strength of a single artifact is limited.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3ｂ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻ and the ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Possible Special Code: 05≻3ｃ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻.
Combining these separate entities created a bridge from Vana'diel to the other realms.
Xarcabard, I'm afraid, is another matter entirely...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Unless the shroud of darkness is lifted, that power alone will not be enough to open the way.
However, the five trophies resonate with another artifact that lies within his land. If we can join our strength to theirs...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Let us make haste to the land where this all began. To Xarcabard...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Is it over...?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: No, the rage has merely been dispersed.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As long as I exist, he will never truly die...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Or perhaps an eternal soul is something beyond the concept of death?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
≺Player Name≻...
You have achieved an incredible feat--the unification of the Shadow Lord has been prevented.
I have not the words to express my gratitude.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The power of the crystal has faded, but I will be drawn into that towering rage no more.
I have heard the voice of the one who holds sway over this realm...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The one who holds sway...?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Yes. From the center of infinite darkness.
I was in a place beyond comprehension when those words reached into my mind...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
You who have touched the crystal, the one who holds immortal power within a mortal shell.
The rage that has arisen from your twisted core will devour my world.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
It was an error in judgment to shelter you...
The order of my realm has been disrupted.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I give to you a duty...
You will stand vigil until an age without hatred has dawned.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
No matter what terrible power you might wield, there is no escape from Dynamis for an incomplete soul.
No return to the land of blessed light...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What manner of being was this who spoke from a pit of blackness?
As this question gnawed at my mind, the voice grew quiet, leaving me in unanswered silence.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Of one thing I was certain.
This voice belonged to the ruler of Dynamis.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: A flow of energy exists in Vana'diel that has escaped the notice of those who dwell there.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Thirty years past, my contact with the crystal caused an accelerated change in this flow.
It was as if it had leapt forward, rushing along a deliberate course.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:

field.Element:Text: The basic rules of Brenner are as follows:≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: First, the participants divide into two teams. Each side's camp contains the same number of “Flammen-Brenner.”≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: At the beginning of the match, half of each side's Flammen-Brenner will be ablaze with “Flamme,” or flame, while the other half will remain unlit.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Participants can seize a Flamme from the opposing side's Flammen-Brenner and carry it around the Isle.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The goal is to steal your opponent's Flamme and use them to light your side's Flammen-Brenner.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The side that succeeds in lighting all of its Flammen-Brenner will be declared the winner after a specified amount of time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If neither side is victorious before the match ends, the outcome will be judged based on the score. The “match score” section of the rulebook contains more information on this subject.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Brenner is significantly divided into public and private matches. Official matches are held periodically according to level and feature general participation.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: You cannot reserve the Isle when an official match is being held.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: No items are necessary for participation, but a minor fee will be collected. You will be unable to participate if your level is too low.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The match outcome will be recorded unless the number of participants fails to exceed ≺Numeric Parameter 0≻ members, or if there are fewer than ≺Numeric Parameter 1≻ members in a match where the two sides' numbers differ. In such cases, the game will be considered a training match and will not be recorded.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Private matches require a reservation, and participation may be limited. The ≺Set Color #5≻Master of Ceremonies≺Set Color #1≻ (MC) can freely adjust the rules and control match proceedings.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: “LS Liga” is a form of private match. You can learn more about LS Liga by speaking to a Marshal.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: A Flammen-Brenner is a device that contains a Flamme (flame). The Flammen-Brenner is covered by a grate that will open after taking a set amount of damage, exposing the Flamme.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The participants must utilize this chance to seize the Flamme before the grate recloses. Once the grate is closed, the Flammen-Brenner will begin recovering from the damage it has been dealt.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If you manage to open the opposing team's Flammen-Brenner and capture their Flamme, you should make haste to light one of the Flammen-Brenner on your side.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: After a certain amount of time, the Flamme will burn out and the opposing team's Flammen-Brenner will be relit.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Also, please note that you cannot quicken your pace using any special abilities while you are in possession of a Flamme.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In the event that neither side fulfills the conditions for victory, the outcome of the match will be evaluated based on score.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ten points are awarded to each side for every lit Flammen-Brenner, while one point is awarded whenever a Flamme is captured, used to light a Flammen-Brenner, or recaptured from an opponent. One point is also awarded for protecting the Flammen-Brenner for a certain period of time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Like Ballista, ≺Set Color #5≻quarry≺Set Color #1≻ (/quarry) can be used while playing Brenner. Participants may use this ability to dig up ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻ and temporary items.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, unlike Ballista Petras, Brenner Petras have no effect on the match score. You can ≺Set Color #5≻trade≺Set Color #1≻ a Petra to a Pursuivant to recover your HP and MP at no expense to TP.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ≺Set Color #5≻Sprint≺Set Color #1≻ cannot be used while carrying a Petra. Also, please note that the ≺Set Color #5≻scout≺Set Color #1≻ ability cannot be used in Brenner.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Petras will be lost in the event of a KO, but can be carried over from one match to another.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The ≺Set Color #5≻sprint≺Set Color #1≻ (/sprint) ability can be used to increase the player's speed when not in possession of a Flamme or Petras.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In the event of a KO, you will be returned to your team's camp. However, recovery will take longer the more often you fall in battle.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In other words, you will receive a penalty if you fall immediately after recovering from KO. In addition, your TP will be reduced to zero and you will lose any Petras in your possession.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I'm sorry. I wasn't listening. Could you start over from the beginning?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What do you wish to know about?
≺Selection Dialog≻Basic rules.
About the ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻.
About ≺Set Color #5≻Sprint≺Set Color #1≻.
About ≺Set Color #5≻Scout≺Set Color #1≻.
About ≺Set Color #5≻Gate Breach≺Set Color #1≻.
About area-specific rules.
About returning to battle.
About special rules.
Nothing at the moment.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ballista is an exercise once used by the San d'Orian armies to train the Royal Knights in the art of the siege. The word “ballista” means “to throw a stone,” and the game has been a part of Vana'dielian military history for centuries.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The rules are simple.
Ballista is played by two teams over a number of hours (Vana'diel time). The team with the most points at the end of the match is the victor.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Players from both teams must search for ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻ that a ≺Set Color #5≻Herald≺Set Color #1≻ has buried in various locations across the battlefield. The players must then take these stones and throw them into targets known as ≺Set Color #5≻Rooks≺Set Color #1≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: These ≺Set Color #5≻Rooks≺Set Color #1≻ can appear in various locations around the battlefield, and both teams are allowed to throw their ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻ into them.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Finally, a player's strength is adjusted depending on his or her level. It is felt that this ultimately allows for a more balanced battle.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻ can be buried anywhere. Once a player believes he or she has found one, the ≺Set Color #5≻Quarry≺Set Color #1≻ (/quarry) command should be used to dig up the area at his or her feet.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Sometimes a player may find items other than ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻, such as potions. These ≺Set Color #5≻temporary items≺Set Color #1≻ can only be used during the current match (or Best of Three series).≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Players can carry more than one ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻, but they cannot throw the stones away once they have obtained them.
However, players will lose their ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻ if they:
(1) Successfully throw them into a rook.
(2) Leave the area.
(3) Are knocked out.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But don't forget, a player will be unable to use the ≺Set Color #5≻Sprint≺Set Color #1≻ command while in possession of a ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻. And, players can only use the ≺Set Color #5≻Scout≺Set Color #1≻ command if they carry one of the stones.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: As one can see, careful planning and impeccable timing are the keys to victory.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: All participants of Ballista will have the ability to use the ≺Set Color #5≻Sprint≺Set Color #1≻ command. This will temporarily increase one's movement speed, creating a better chance to find and obtain ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, remember that once a player has obtained a ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻, he or she will be unable to use the ≺Set Color #5≻Sprint≺Set Color #1≻ command. In its place, though, one may use the ≺Set Color #5≻Scout≺Set Color #1≻ command.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The locations of the ≺Set Color #5≻Rooks≺Set Color #1≻ are constantly changing. This makes it quite difficult to find the targets by just randomly walking about the area.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Communication with one's team members is, of course, one way to locate ≺Set Color #5≻Rooks≺Set Color #1≻. However, another way is by using the ≺Set Color #5≻Scout≺Set Color #1≻ command. This will inform a player of the approximate location of the nearest ≺Set Color #5≻Rook≺Set Color #1≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Finally, ≺Set Color #5≻Scout≺Set Color #1≻ can only be used when a player is carrying a ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻. Because ≺Set Color #5≻Sprint≺Set Color #1≻ cannot be used at this time, players must be weary of approaching enemies.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: So, a ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻ has been obtained and a ≺Set Color #5≻Rook≺Set Color #1≻ located. Now all that's left is tossing the stone in, right? Wrong.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is one aspect of Ballista that has yet to be mentioned...and this is where the real battle begins.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: To throw a ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻ into a ≺Set Color #5≻Rook≺Set Color #1≻, a player must first wait until the ≺Set Color #5≻Rook's≺Set Color #1≻ gate is open. This takes impeccable timing, as the gate is only open for a short while.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
But not just anyone can score points this way. A player must first take down a member of the opposing team and achieve ≺Set Color #5≻Gate Breach≺Set Color #1≻ status.
Only then will his or her shots count.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: This extreme method of combat is what made the ancient game of Ballista famous, and transformed its participants into heroes.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Running about looking for stones is no different from a child's game of hide-and-seek. Knowing when to strike is what separates the men from the boys.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The following match types are area-specific:
All or Nothing (one match) * Normal Items Allowed: Jugner Forest
All or Nothing (one match) * Normal Items Restricted: Pashhow Marshlands
Best of Three (three matches) * Normal Items Allowed: Meriphataud Mountains≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
≺Set Color #5≻Best of Three≺Set Color #1≻ series rules are as follows:
Winning a match will earn a nation one “match point.” The nation with the most match points at the end of the series will be declared the victor. Winning the third and final match and producing the high scorer will result in two match points awarded. This allows both sides the chance for “come-from-behind” victories.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Between each of the matches, a short interval will be implemented. During this interval, Invisible and Sneak will be cast on all participants. We suggest this time be used to discuss strategies with the other members of your nation's forces.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Players will be forbidden from using any items they bring to the battlefield. Only temporary items that are quarried may be used. A total of fifteen temporary items (though only one of each type) can be carried.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: When this rule is in effect, all players will be presented with five complimentary temporary items at the beginning of the match.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: For more information on temporary items, refer to the “special rules.”≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: After being KO'd, if a player chooses to be revived at the spot he was defeated, 100% of all HP and 50% of all MP will be restored. In addition, the player will maintain 50% of the TP he had earned.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If a player chooses to return to their force's camp, HP and MP will be fully restored, but all TP will be lost.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Please note that many of the rules previously considered “special” have been fully implemented.
Also, several new special rules have been added.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Learn about which special rules?
≺Selection Dialog≻≺Set Color #5≻Temporary items≺Set Color #1≻.
Ballista Points.
Scoring restrictions.
≺Set Color #5≻Gate Breach≺Set Color #1≻ radius expansion.
Resistance to Sleep.
Open entries.
Minimum level restrictions.
Re-entry restrictions.
Participant & Rook numbers.
Experience Points.
Return.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Previously, participants in Ballista were required to use an item the moment they dug it up using the /quarry command. However, players can now stock these items as ≺Set Color #5≻temporary items≺Set Color #1≻ for use at any time during the match.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Players can hold up to ten ≺Set Color #5≻temporary items≺Set Color #1≻, but only one of each type. If a player finds an item that they already possess, they must use it immediately or throw it away.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If players who possess ten ≺Set Color #5≻temporary items≺Set Color #1≻ find an item that they have not already obtained, they will also have the option to exchange it with one of their current items.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Also, players will not, at any time, be allowed to trade temporary items. However, there are items that can be used on other Ballista participants. Please note that players may not be able to use these special items as soon as they are quarried.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Finally, the Heralds will collect ≺Set Color #5≻temporary items≺Set Color #1≻ when the match (the third in a Best of Three series) has concluded.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ballista Points are rewarded to each competitor based on his or her performance in a single Ballista match. The maximum number of points that can be accumulated per match is ≺Numeric Parameter 0≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: While it is taken into consideration, scoring ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻ is not the only way to earn Ballista Points. Assisting allies and defeating members of the enemy forces can also earn a high score.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ballista Points can be traded for special “vouchers,” which may be exchanged for free ≺Set Color #5≻temporary items≺Set Color #1≻ at the start of new matches.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
However, remember that depending on the level restriction of the match, certain vouchers will not be redeemed at the beginning of a match.
Speak with a ≺Set Color #5≻Marshal≺Set Color #1≻ directly after a match to register your points.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Players will only be allowed to score up to five ≺Set Color #5≻Petras≺Set Color #1≻ at a time. Also, a player's ≺Set Color #5≻Gate Breach≺Set Color #1≻ status will be automatically disengaged if a ≺Set Color #5≻Petra≺Set Color #1≻ is not scored within a certain amount of time. The amount of time is increased for those members of the team currently behind in points.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: All allies within a certain radius will achieve ≺Set Color #5≻Gate Breach≺Set Color #1≻ status when a member of the enemy forces is defeated.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Players' resistance to sleep will be increased.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: During the entry period, from ≺Numeric Parameter 0≻:≺Unknown Parameter (Type: 94) 1≻, all adventurers will be allowed to join the forces with the smallest number of participants, regardless of allegiance. Open entries will be accepted until both sides have reached maximum capacity.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
In order to ensure balanced matches, the following level limits are enforced:
Level 30 matches: 1～30≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Level 40 matches: 31～40
Level 50 matches: 41～50
Level 60 matches: 51～60
Unrestricted matches: 61～≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Please note that any participant who cancels his or her registration will not be allowed to re-apply for the same match.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: When the total number of participants in a match is less than 40, the location of the two camps will be adjusted. Also in this case, the number of Rooks will be reduced to two.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Any adventurer whose main level is over 30 will receive EXP for participating in a Ballista match. However, no EXP will be rewarded if the adventurer fails to actively take part in the match.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Read which chapter on B.P. Ranking?
≺Selection Dialog≻Basic Information.
Registering Points.
Rewards.
Chevron & Title List.
None.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ballista Point Ranking is based upon all Ballista Points registered from the past ten matches in each of the three participating battle areas.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Anyone who wishes to take part in the ranking needs to register ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[his/her] points within four hours (Vana'diel time) from the end of the previous match.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: After the registration period ends, players can compare their record with those of the previous nine matches.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: If, at any time, a player ranks in the top ten (overall) or first for a specific job, ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[he/she] will have the opportunity to receive a special ≺Set Color #5≻chevron≺Set Color #1≻ as well as a new ≺Set Color #5≻title≺Set Color #1≻.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There are four types of chevrons and titles awarded to top-ten players (gold/mythril/silver/bronze), as well as twenty different types awarded for outstanding performances by players of each of the twenty jobs.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Wearing a chevron during a Ballista match will automatically change a player's current title. If a player wishes to possess this title after a match as well, ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[he/she] must contact a certain bard in San d'Oria.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Also, while wearing a chevron, players will be able to trade Ballista Points for temporary items not available to all players.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: However, the rules of Ballista state that players may only possess a certain chevron for no longer than one half Vana'diel year. When that time comes, they are required to return the chevron before being allowed to participate in any further matches.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Finally, ≺Set Color #5≻checking≺Set Color #1≻ someone during a Ballista match will display the total number of chevrons that person has accumulated to date.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I'm a traveling Moogle, always on the road... In search of the secrets of true strength, kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: And this time I think I might have found one. That's why I'm visiting Maat to see what he thinks, kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: I could fill you in on the details, but you don't look like you'd understand what I have to say. Come back when you think you've got some more seasoning under your belt, kupo...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I've discovered a way to increase the potential of those who have reached their “limits.” However, I haven't found anyone to pass that method on to, kupo.
Hey, you look pretty tough. How would you like to be my guinea...errr, assistant?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Wait a minute! I remember you!
I already filled you in on the secrets of the Moogle Merit Management system, kupo! Stop wasting your time here; get fighting, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Become his “assistant”?
≺Selection Dialog≻Let's do it!
No way!
Tell me more...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Excellent, kupo...
Ahem! I shall now pass on to you the secrets of the “Moogle Merit Management” system. Use this legendary method to extend your limits. Watch as your strength soars beyond the stars, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Now, when the level of your main job has reached 75 or higher, a new button, “Merit Points,” will appear under “Status” in the main menu.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Press this button to change experience accumulation modes as well as adjust skills and attributes. Just remember, you can only adjust your attributes while in your Mog House or Mog Garden, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ≺Speaker Name≻ casts a strange spell on you...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Hmmm... That didn't work, kupo...
I guess I still have some research to do. We'll have to put the experiment on hold for a while.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Huh? What good is an adventurer that's not willing to take on a little adventure?
Well, come back to me if you ever change your mind, kupo...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Been working hard, or hardly working, kupo?
Remember that by pressing the “Merit Points” button in the “Status” menu, you can check merit point totals, change experience accumulation modes, and adjust skills and attributes.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Oho, kupo! Or perhaps you're looking to transcend your limits?
Because that could also be arranged...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Ask about merit points?
≺Selection Dialog≻Yes.
No.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
What will you ask about?
≺Selection Dialog≻Exceeding your limits.
Merit points.
Nothing.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, if you ever need a refresher, you know where I'll be, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Or perhaps you've finally mustered the courage to conquer your inner limits, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Before you rush into anything, let me inform you of the disclaim...errr, the details of the method, kupo.
Have you ever stopped to wonder what happens to all the experience you accumulate after maxing out your level?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In recent months, I have discovered that this type of experience builds up in your body in a completely different form--a type of super experience, if you will. I have given this phenomenon the name ≺Set Color #5≻limit points≺Set Color #1≻, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: When you accumulate ten thousand of these points, they are magically transformed into an even more super type of experience--super-duper experience, if you will. I call these ultra-special points “merit points,” kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: But that is not all I have discovered. I think I have also come across a method to manage those points and use them to boost the levels of your body and mind beyond their current limits! I call it “Moogle Merit Management,” kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
I can tell by the look on your face that you're pretty interested, kupo.
So, what would you like to know?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Ask about...
≺Selection Dialog≻How to accumulate merit points.
How to adjust attributes.
Nothing at this time.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, you already know that by reaching level 75 you're ready to start collecting limit points, right, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Well, before you begin, don't forget that you have to press the “Merit Points” button in the “Status” menu.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It only appears when your main job is level 75 or higher, kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: By pressing this button, you can toggle between “experience point accumulation mode” and “limit point accumulation mode,” kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In experience point accumulation mode, you will gain normal EXP after every battle until you reach the maximum...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: ...while in limit point accumulation mode, you will receive limit points after every battle. It's that easy, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, and by the way--if you are still in experience point accumulation mode after you've reached your maximum amount of EXP, any battles fought from that moment on will earn you limit points, regardless of the mode you are in, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Normally, you can only accumulate limit points when you're playing a job that has reached level 75 or higher. However, there is one exception, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: When a job capable of receiving limit points has been reduced via a level restriction, you can still earn limit points by defeating enemies!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Just don't forget to switch modes before heading out on a hunting trip! When you're in limit point accumulation mode, the color of the text in the “Status” window will change a little to let you know, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Finally, if you level down or switch jobs while in limit point accumulation mode, you will automatically be switched back to experience point accumulation mode.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ah, and one more point of advice: You can always check the amount of limit points and merit points you have earned by viewing the “Merit Point” menu.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Ummm, first of all, you can check the number of merit points you have accumulated by pressing the “Merit Points” button under “Status” in the main menu.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: The data I have collected so far tells me that it is quite difficult to raise these attributes, and that there seems to be a limit to the amount any certain attribute can be boosted, kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: It also seems that certain attributes and skills are connected in some way. I call these groups “categories.”≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: For example, imagine the attributes in the “HP/MP” category can be raised a ≺Set Color #5≻“combination”≺Set Color #1≻ of seven times, kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: That means if you raise your “Max HP” five times, you can only raise your “Max MP” two times.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: In other words, you cannot raise all of the attributes to their limits. The body must maintain a certain balance, or it will explode! Or something like that, kupo.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: There is also a way to lower attributes that have been pushed past their limits. Unfortunately, every time this is tried, the merit points used to originally raise that attribute are lost, kupo...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Oh, and finally, there are some attributes and skills in the same category that have different limits. I'm still not sure about all of these, so I'd suggest asking some of your level 75 buddies for advice, kupo!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Hrm?
Hmmm...
I need a little time alone to think...
Would you mind coming back a little later, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

I had a feeling that's what you'd say, kupo!
Well, Maat? How about it?≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: We stand on the cusp of a new era. It's the Goddess-given duty of an old warrior like me to prepare the younger generation to follow in my footsteps. And who better than a young ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[man/woman] who's met every challenge sent ≺Multiple Choice (Player Gender)≻[his/her] way?≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: You can say that again, my friend!≺Prompt≻

field.Element:Text: No doubt you've heard of the mog tablets--those stone slabs engraved with the timeless wisdom of King Kupofried the Great that have been popping up periodically throughout the land.≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
The tablets hold many secrets that we moogles have yet to unravel, kupo.
Why are our wings purple? Why are our noses red? How can we better assist our adventuring friends?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: Why, I was just having a discussion with a friend of mine from the Magian Mooglehood on the very subject... That's when it hit me on the head like a herd of hecteyes!≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text: What if the ancient moogle arts could be used to augment not only adventurers' possessions, but the adventurers themselves, kupo!?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Using my knowledge of merit points--and drawing upon the martial mastery of Maat here--I've whipped up a method that just might work!
What say you, adventurer? Care to be my test subject?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
'Course, nobody'd blame you for not trustin' the little devil.
I'm not even sure I do. Heh heh heh...≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Is an adventurer who would spurn greater strength truly an adventurer?
Come, now! What have you got to lose, kupo?≺Prompt≻
field.Attribute:name: text

field.Element:Text:
Give it a go, kupo?
≺Selection Dialog≻Will I ever!
Not today.≺Prompt≻

Marvelous! Magnificent!
First, I'll need you to bring me ≺Numeric Parameter 1≻ ≺Possible Special Code: 01≻≺Speaker Name≻)ａ≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 8280≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻≺BAD CHAR: 80≻.≺Prompt≻
